LAGOS – The final home journey for former Secretary General of the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) Chief Taiwo Ogunjobi begins on Wednesday (today) with a symposium at the auditorium of the Lekan Salami Stadium, Adamasingba, Ibadan with top football administrators like Amanze Uchegbulam, Dr. Bolaji Ojo-Oba as well as Chief Segun Odegbami as speakers. Later in the day, there will be a football match featuring his former club, Shooting Stars Sports Club (3SC) of Ibadan and the later club he administered as the Osun State FA boss, the Osun United. These events were put together by the Western Nigeria Football Forum (WNFF) being marshalled by the NFF first vice president, Seyi Akinwunmi. On Thursday, another football match is on the card. It will feature a Whatsapp discussion group, “Family United by Sports” – FUBS and Ibadan All Stars – an assembly of retired footballers. According to the Oyo State Commissioner for Youth and Sports, Yomi Oke, the lying in state will take place at the main bowl of the Lekan Salami Stadium, Adamasingba Ibadan on Thursday before a Christian Wake-Keep while church service comes up at Living Spring Church, Ojoo Ibadan, before his body will be committed to earth on Friday, March 15.